prompt_template:
Analyse the following index/ETF for a decade-scale value investor.

INDEX: {index_name} ({index_ticker})
Type: {index_type}
Currency: {currency}
As of: {as_of_date}

--- PRICE / LEVEL ---
Current level: {current_level}
52-week range: {low_52w} – {high_52w}
1-day change: {change_1d_pct}

--- RETURNS ---
YTD:    {return_ytd}
1 month: {return_1m}
3 months: {return_3m}
1 year: {return_1y}
3 year (ann.): {return_3y_ann}
5 year (ann.): {return_5y_ann}

--- RISK ---
1Y annualised volatility: {volatility_1y_ann}

--- VALUATION ---
Weighted P/E: {weighted_pe}
Dividend yield: {dividend_yield}

--- ETF DETAILS (if applicable) ---
AUM: {aum}
Expense ratio: {expense_ratio}

--- TOP HOLDINGS ---
{top_holdings_table}

--- SECTOR WEIGHTS ---
{sector_weights_table}

--- COUNTRY WEIGHTS ---
{country_weights_table}

Write a structured investment analysis. Respond ONLY with a valid JSON object — no prose outside the JSON.

JSON schema:
{
  "index_overview": "<2-3 sentences: what this index is, its geography and sector focus>",
  "composition_quality": "<paragraph: constituent quality, sector/country concentration, mega-cap skew>",
  "performance_summary": "<paragraph: returns context, consistency, comparison to inflation/benchmarks>",
  "valuation_assessment": "<paragraph: cheap/fair/expensive, P/E context, dividend support>",
  "risk_profile": "<paragraph: concentration risk, volatility, macro sensitivities>",
  "macro_context": "<paragraph: relevant macro backdrop for this index today>",
  "long_horizon_verdict": "<paragraph: would a decade-scale value investor find this attractive, and why>",
  "recommendation": "<ACCUMULATE | HOLD | REDUCE>",
  "recommendation_rationale": "<1-2 sentences: the core reason for the recommendation>"
}
